WikifierOutput.InputText: News Lima to Direct Live-Action Tom Thumb Source: October 8, 2008 Warner Bros. and Red Wagon have lined up Kevin Lima ( Enchanted ) to direct Tom Thumb , a live-action take on the origins of the tiny character. Red Wagon's Doug Wick and Lucy Fisher will produce, with Chris Chase executive producing. The story, written by Robert Rodat ( Saving Private Ryan ), is centered on an arrogant knight who's shrunk to 6 inches while assigned to protect a princess and then discovers what it means to be a real hero. Variety says Warner Bros. is aiming to develop the film as a tentpole project with worldwide appeal. | | Comments Posted by: MovieFan83 on October 8, 2008 at 02:19:35 Sounds totally different to the 1958 original! I thought that was a classic! We'll wait and see what happens here...
